name: ClassesUSA.com
overview: ClassesUSA.com, Inc. operates as an online higher-education portal. It provides content on various topics, including online associate, bachelor’s, master’s, and post-graduate degrees; and online certificate programs, traditional college and university degrees, career school degrees and programs, education financing, and test preparation. ClassesUSA.com, Inc. has strategic partnership with msn, Sprinks, msn Learning & Research Encarta, salary com, google, AOL.com, Lycos, Inc.com, Yahoo, Fastcompany.com, Overture, Cox television, Yahoo education, Entrepreneur.com, Ask jeeves, JBS, Findwhat.com, Real cities network, What you need to know About, Tribune Interactive, Washingtonpost.com, Quigo, NBC, Kanoodle.com, Vault, Barnes & Noble Uiversity, Looksmart, and Weather.com. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in New York, New York. As of July 26, 2005, ClassesUSA.com, Inc. is a subsidiary of Experian Information Solutions, Inc.
